church:
    play sound click
    if (== $stats.day.value 2):
        choice:
            "The spire of Bluehills Cathedral calls to you. In your chest you feel it, rings, rings, rings."
            "[Bathe in holy ambience and maybe meet a weird gangly woman] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>":
                play sound spendAction
                set data.game_map.inMap false
                add_stat actions -1
                set_button button_church false
                run transition_black church
                clear_dialog
            "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
                jump game_map
    else:
        choice:
            "The spire of Bluehills Cathedral calls to you. In your chest you feel it, rings, rings, rings."
            "[Bathe in holy ambience] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>":
                play sound spendAction
                set data.game_map.inMap false
                add_stat actions -1
                set_button button_church false
                run transition_instant church
                clear_dialog
            "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
                jump game_map

    "The cathedral is a shadow of its former self, quite literally, for there is not enough manpower left in the congregation to keep the candles alight."
    "Were it not for the sunrise streaming through the stained-glass windows the great hall would be as gloomy as a basement."
    "Only a small congregation still huddles together at the far end of the great hall. The columns that stretch into the distance are engraved with an endless list of names."
    if (roll church_names_orb orb 40):
        choice:
            talk orb talk "The names of those recorded to have joined Saint Dawnsight on her crusade. Kings, knights, craftsmen, jesters, scholars, priests and peasants alike. A dance macabre. Their names are remembered equally, and forever."
            "Why are some of the names written in gold?":
                talk orb talk "Those are the kings and the knights. I used the phrase <span class='writtenText'>'equally'</span> a little too liberally, sorry."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    if (roll church_magnificent_orb orb 20):
        choice:
            talk orb talk "This hall was magnificent, once upon a time. The congregation would fill the pews, the standing space and even stretch outside, on occasion. The acoustics created by the architecture broadcast the speaker's voice from above and behind them, as if from the stained glass saint herself."
            "Where did everyone go?":
                talk orb talk "Some were taken by the plague, but most by the war."
                clear_dialog
                talk orb talk "The Anglian church was a vital cog in the nation's propaganda machine. It preached the glory of fighting alongside your church friends against the evils of Brennenburg and its religion that is *oh* so dismissive of Saint Dawnsight, who may we remind you, fought her war without complaining. Did her duty."
                clear_dialog
                talk orb talk "The congregation bled into the mud, watched their town burn under bombs, watched their saint do nothing when their families were butchered by corvidaen rabies."
                talk orb talk "Those who did not lose their life lost their faith and those who did not lose their faith lost their trust in the institution."
                talk orb talk "Those whose devotion to the tightly defined scripture the church preaches? They are who you see before you. A handful of zealots. A scattering of indomitable ants."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "The cathedral feels familiar, somehow. Something tickles at your brain."
    if (roll church_before_orb orb 60):
        talk orb talk "You've haven't been here before, but during your childhood you were often dragged along to a similar cathedral someplace else."
        talk orb talk "Your parents weren't devoutly religious, the formality of the Anglian church was always off-putting for them, but they would take you with them a few times a year when the mood took them."
    else:
        wait 1000
    if (== $stats.day.value 2):
        clear_dialog
        "A pale fox sits alone towards the back of the great hall. She is not part of the congregation; she is an anomaly. She glances towards you, and then towards a spread of cards in her hand, comparing you to them as if that were a completely normal thing to do to a total stranger."
    jump church_menu

church_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The windows shimmer. The colours reflected off of a stream on a summers day."
        "[Approach the mysterious card shuffling fox]" if (&& (!= $data.church.sinnerMet true) (== $stats.day.value 2)):
            jump church_sinnerIntro
        "[Gaze into the window at the end of the cathedral]":
            run transition church_window_centre
            set data.church.lookingAt "center"
            jump church_window
        "Bored now. I'm leaving forever. <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            if (&& (!= $data.church.sinnerMet true) (== $stats.day.value 2)):
                choice:
                    talk nasty talk "Hark, we have yet to speak to the slightly off-putting woman I madly want to kiss. I beseech thee, Ghost, reconsider leaving just yet."
                    "Kiss, you say? <span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
                        jump church_menu
                    "Don't care didn't ask plus you're down bad. <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
                        play sound spendAction
                        talk nasty talk "Fuck you. Fuck you."
            if (!= $data.church.lookedAtWindow true):
                "Your hand grips something. A sword. Flames curl across it. You look down. There is nothing."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk lovely talk "Gasp! You aren't really going to leave without paying your respects to her holiness, are you, Ghost?"
                    "I suppose not. She *does* look very pretty... <span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
                        jump church_menu
                    "F. There you go, Lovely Lady. <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
                        play sound spendAction
                        talk lovely talk "Heathen..."
            if (objective_started? dawnsight shrine):
                clear_dialog
                "A feeling inside. Unfurling. Unfurling. In the woods <span class='gold'>she</span> waits for you..."
            complete_objective church church
            if (!= $data.church.lookedAtWindow true):
                if $data.church.sinnerMet:
                    complete_quest church churchSuccessSinner
                else:
                    complete_quest church churchSuccessVisit
            else:
                complete_quest church churchSuccess
            jump goToGameMap

church_sinnerIntro:
    run transition church_sinner
    set data.church.sinnerMet true
    "The 'mysterious card shuffling fox' eyes you suspiciously."
    if (roll church_sinnerIntro_suspicion_lovely lovely 40):
        talk lovely talk "It's not genuine suspicion; she's glad you've approached her. She's been trying to get your attention since you arrived."
        if (roll church_sinnerIntro_fuck_nasty nasty 40):
            talk nasty talk "She wants to FUCK."
            talk lovely talk "She wants to *talk*."
            if (roll church_sinnerIntro_either_orb orb 20):
                talk orb talk "She'll settle for either."
            else:
                wait 1000
        else:
            wait 1000
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "May I help you?"
        "[Sit next to her]":
            play sound clothing
            "A smile flickers on her face, just for a moment."
        "\\"May I sit next to you?\\"":
            "A mean smile flickers on her face, just for a moment."
            if (roll church_sinnerIntro_sit_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "She's glad you want to sit next to her, and gladder still that you felt you had to ask."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "You may."
        "\\"Sorry. I'll leave. Sorry.\\"":
            talk sinner talk "No. Stay. Please."
            if (roll church_sinnerIntro_unwelcome_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "She's annoyed that her suspicious glance actually made you feel unwelcome. She didn't mean for that to happen."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "She smells familiar. A neuron hidden somewhere in your brain attempts to sputter back to life, but fails. Some kind of wine, perhaps?"
    if (roll church_sinnerIntro_wine_lovely lovely 20):
        talk lovely talk "'Chateaux Saint-Arnoin'. It clings to her like perfume, because she intentionally splashes a little on herself every morning."
        if (roll church_sinnerIntro_wine_orb orb 20):
            talk orb talk "It's vintage nineteen-fifteen. Not expensive, but not exactly cheap either."
            talk nasty talk "Imagine spending dosh on wine when vodka and lighter fluid exist. Always be hustling."
        else:
            wait 1000
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "There's something more. Oestradiol. She smokes it often. It gives the red wine a dry, minty undertone. It's rather intoxicating, but then, everything about the pale fox beside you is. The night black fur surrounding her pink eyes most of all."
    if (roll church_sinnerIntro_tired_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "The black fur around her eyes is natural, but even if it was white from birth it would be black now. She runs a sleep debt that only goes up. One day soon the collector will collect, and they will not be kind about it."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "She folds the cards away into a small case, which she hides in her coat pocket."
    if (roll church_sinnerIntro_multitask_lovely lovely 20):
        talk lovely talk "She isn't shy about... whatever she was doing, but she knows all too well she cannot multitask."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    run transition church_sinner_ghost
    talk sinner talk "Do you come here often? I don't recognise you."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "Her voice is soft, transexual. Stern, but inviting. A hint of performance to it. Somewhere between singer and practised radio news reader."
        "\\"I don't think so, no.\\"":
            "She eyes you curiously. <span class='writtenText'>'I don't think so'</span> was not an answer she expected."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "Then what brought you here today then, pray tell?"
                "\\"I don't know.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "You don't seem to know much, do you?"
                    talk sinner talk "Not that I don't envy you... still, it happens..."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk sinner talk "I'd be remiss to claim I don't often wander aimlessly devoid of any tangible goal. Places of worship are like magnets for us people, aren't they?"
                        "\\"What brought *you* here?\\"":
                            run skip
                "\\"Vibes.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Mhm, yes. I'm here for much the same reason; to bathe in the ambience, so to speak."
                roll church_sinnerIntro_girls_nasty nasty 40 "Hunting for girls. You know how it is.":
                    success ""
                        "The Sinner smirks."
                        clear_dialog
                        choice:
                            talk sinner talk "Any luck?"
                            "\\"I've had some now.\\" [Wink embarrassingly]":
                                "She smiles, but it's somewhat empty."
                            "\\"Not really, no.\\"":
                                "She raises an eyebrow."
                                clear_dialog
                                talk nasty talk "Nice neg."
                                clear_dialog
                                talk sinner talk "Girls are a fine reason for most activities. I wish you luck."
                    failure ""
                        "The Sinner raises an eyebrow."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk nasty talk "Say it with some conviction next time, jackass."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk sinner talk "For my part? I am merely attending service to bathe in the ambience, so to speak."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "She continues to stare into the coloured glass, fixated upon it as though she might find the Divine itself looking back at her through it."
        "\\"It's a nice cathedral, I guess.\\"":
            talk sinner talk "It is, isn't it? It reeks of a humility that lingers like a miasma punctuated only occasionally by flashes of glorious, overwhelming beauty, yes?"
            if (roll church_sinnerIntro_cathedral_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "She describes the cathedral as though she's trying really hard to describe a fine wine."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            "The Sinner looks away from the window that seems to fascinate her so, and into *you*."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "And yet..."
            clear_dialog
            "She smiles. Her eyes flicker shut, a second too slowly to hide the tears forming in them."
            if (roll church_sinnerIntro_cries_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "She cries a lot. Everyday."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "I feel nothing. Elasia does not speak to me. The Divine has no place for me. I am not supposed to be here. <span class='writtenText'>'Here'</span> being in a cosmic sense."
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner turns away from you, annoyed at her own brief moment of vulnerability. She clears her throat before continuing."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "Still, it's no surprise I haven't seen you here before, if indeed you so rarely attend mass. I must admit I have only been here on a handful of occasions, having only moved to Bluehills perhaps three months ago. I was..."
    if (roll church_sinnerIntro_melodramatic_lovely lovely 60):
        talk lovely talk "This pause is intentional. She's being melodramatic. Again."
        talk nasty talk "That's a Lovely Lady trait, I think."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "...unsatisfied with my previous home. The corpse of a dead, dying mining town did not suit me."
        "\\"Dead *and* dying?\\"":
            talk sinner talk "The people are dead, the town is dying."
            jump church_sinnerBriargrey
        "\\"Corpse?\\"":
            talk sinner talk "Because it's dead, yes."
            clear_dialog
            talk lovely talk "Dead AND a corpse? I'm seeing a lot of repetition here."
            talk nasty talk "Dead AND a corpse? I'm seeing a lot of repetition here."
            talk lovely talk "Hey! Cease your antics, Nasty Girl!"
            talk nasty talk "Hey! Cease your antics, Nasty Girl!"
            talk lovely talk "AAAARGH!"
            talk nasty talk "AAAARGH!"
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "Shut up shut up shut up shut up shut up."
            jump church_sinnerBriargrey
        "\\"Where are you from?\\"":
            jump church_sinnerBriargrey

church_sinnerBriargrey:
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner fishes around for something in her coat pocket for a moment before snapping back to your conversation."
    if (roll church_sinnerBriargrey_smoking_lovely lovely 20):
        talk lovely talk "She was subconsciously reaching for her lighter. Smoking has been strictly forbidden in the church since the incident, but were it not she would be lighting a cigarette right now."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "I'm from Briargrey. You've probably heard of it."
    if (roll church_sinnerBriarfrey_memory_orb orb 80):
        set data.church.knowsBirargrey true
        talk orb talk "A mining accident. The town was partially flattened. A lot of people died."
        talk orb talk "The north side of the town, where the landslide met the community, is deserted now."
        clear_dialog
        talk orb talk "There is only rubble and ruin left behind. Depression bleeds from it. A grey and black pus that had found its way into the gut of everyone who lived there."
        talk orb talk "The entire side of town had been fenced off once, now only the rotting posts stand testament to that, they had never been replaced. They do not need to be. People do not desire to trespass this place."
        talk orb talk "A tractor sits in the middle of the desolation, a trailer of rubble still towed behind it. It is rusted now, practically part of the environment. It was left there after the recovery effort ended. Discarded like a contaminated scalpel after gut surgery."
        clear_dialog
        talk orb talk "The houses that once stood there are gone now. Small remnants of wall, perhaps the occasional chimney are all that remains of them."
        talk orb talk "Who had lived there? What treasures, keepsakes and precious memories had they been decorated with?"
        clear_dialog
        talk orb talk "Gods... it's a lot sadder when I put it into words... when it lived up in my database it was just information, now it's real... the barbarity... the lack of justice..."
        clear_dialog
        talk orb talk "Ahem. Anyway. Mining accidents uh... they..."
        clear_dialog
        talk orb talk "It happened at ten in the morning. A crisp autumn day, much like this one."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The woman fiddles with one of her necklaces. A golden crown. Its sides are worn from her incessant fiddling."
        "\\"What happened to Briargrey?\\"":
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "A mining incident. A bad one. The journalists, they all use the phrase accident, but it wasn't. It was the logical conclusion of a decade of documented corporate mismanagement. It was murder."
                "\\"What was?\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Briargrey was once a prosperous coal mining town, until 1926, not long after the end of the war, when the spoil tip which had, for various <span class='writtenText'>'economic'</span> reasons, been kept atop the hill on the north side of the town, collapsed and brought most of the hillside with it."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "One-hundred-eighty-seven dead townspeople were a front page story for a day, and then they were forgotten."
                    if (roll church_sinnerBriargrey_spoil_orb orb 20):
                        talk orb talk "A spoil tip is a mound of excavated rubble removed from the mine. It's worthless, and can end up piling quite high, just for your information."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
        "\\"The mining accident. Half the town was flattened. People died. I think. Am I thinking of the right mining disaster?\\"" if $data.church.knowsBirargrey:
            talk sinner talk "You are, yes. The spoil tip collapsed and took one-hundred-eighty-seven people with it."
    clear_dialog
    "The recollection of a national tragedy brings a dour mood to the conversation, which seems to float upside down in its aquarium."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "Anyhow. I best be off. The day has finally crawled out of its pit, and I can't sit here all day while I have research to attend to. The sermon at the far end of the cathedral continues in its absence. There is not time for silence while we yet pray for her return."
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner flashes her teeth."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "It was nice to meet you, Ms..."
        "\\"Ghost. For now, anyway.\\"":
            talk sinner talk "Charming."
    clear_dialog
    play sound clothing
    "She stands, and without so much as looking at you disappears from the gloomy cathedral and into the daylight."
    run transition church_nosinner
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "You should check your pocket. Trust me."
        "[Check your pocket]":
            jump church_pocket
        "No.":
            choice:
                talk orb talk "What? Why?"
                "I just don't feel like it! I don't know! Stop pressuring me! You're stressing me out / making me anxious etc!":
                    talk orb talk "Whatever, suit yourself. Idiot. Let's just miss out on an entire storyline. Who fucking cares."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk nasty talk "Yonder storyline mayhap climax in us fucking. Prithee I beg thee reconsider m'lady."
                        "Fine. Whatever. [Check your pocket]":
                            jump church_pocket
                "Fine. Whatever. [Check your pocket]":
                    jump church_pocket
                    
church_pocket:
    play sound clothing
    run transition church_card
    start_quest sinner
    "Nestled snuggly in your pocket is a card, it's not one of the cards from The Sinner's deck, it's a card for a wine merchant. An address has been scrawled across it in ink. <span class='writtenText'>'Apartment 1, 13 Rosethorn Lane'</span>."
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Gasp! H- how did that get in our pocket!? My goodness! Was that!? Magic!? Oh that! That! That dame!"
    if (roll church_sinnerBriargrey_magic_orb orb 40):
        talk orb talk "It was a magic trick, which while visually similar to actual magic, is *not* actual magic."
        talk lovely talk "A witch... how exciting!"
        clear_dialog
        talk nasty talk "I'd like to show her a trick or two. With my tongue, that is. Wahey!"
        talk lovely talk "Ugh. You are simply beastly, Nasty Girl."
        talk orb talk "You two are idiots and I hate you both."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    run transition church
    jump church_menu

church_window:
    set data.church.lookedAtWindow true
    "There are three windows at the end of the cathedral. Each a different depiction of Queen Marigold Elasia Dawnsight, The Queen who bravely led her great crusade into the swirling dark to slay the demon that choked the world."
    "The Anglian church holds that she was successful in this feat."
    if (roll church_window_volcano_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "She wasn't. Her demon was a volcano, her crusade was naive folly, and she froze to death with a lung that was more ash than bronchi."
        talk orb talk "When the knowledge of the super volcano was later brought to Anglia it was seen as merely the site of the battle, where depending on interpretation, the queen either continues to battle for eternity, or rests peacefully."
        talk orb talk "Either way the end of the Dark Age was seen as indisputable proof of her divinity. In the absence of a body she lives on eternal. The soul of an empty people."
    else:
        wait 1000
    jump church_window_menu

church_window_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The stained glass shimmers pleasantly in the morning sun. Part of you wishes you could sit and stare at it forever, but it would probably lose its charm around sundown."
        "[Look at the centre window]":
            jump church_window_centre
        "[Look at the left window]":
            jump church_window_left
        "[Look at the right window]":
            jump church_window_right
        "<span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            run transition church
            jump church_menu

church_window_centre:
    if (!= $data.church.lookingAt "center"):
        run transition church_window_centre
    set data.church.lookingAt "center"
    "Saint Marigold Elasia Dawnsight."
    "She's beautiful."
    clear_dialog
    "<span class='goldItalic'>Golden light</span>. Unfurling. Warm breath on your throat."
    clear_dialog
    "The peaks of her crown, the symbol of the church of Anglia, shine like beacons in the night. Her golden hair flows from her scalp and forms a sea of warm curls that frame her. It is more than just hair, it is an aura, the golden glow of the Divine."
    "She wields the divine spear, 'Lightsinger', with a mixture of confidence and humility. It is the heart of her followers, the heart of Anglia, the heart of all the peoples of the world. She cradles it like a child. So long as she is close to it, and they close to her, the Divine will always prevail over darkness."
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "Anglia's saviour. The *worlds* saviour. So the church would have you believe, at least."
    jump church_window_centre_menu

church_window_centre_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The sunrise shines through Dawnsight's golden locks. Divine light. A <span class='goldItalic'>warmth</span> that compels you to speak to her. White feathers... white feathers..."
        "Do people pray to her?" if (!= $data.church.prayed true):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "They do. It began during the Dark Age, shortly after she departed on her crusade. It was a one-way transaction of good fortune to her, but as she failed to return and the dark age dragged on these prayers morphed into pleading for her victory, pleading for her to bring good fortune and eventually begging for anything."
                "[Pray to Saint Dawnsight]":
                    set data.church.prayed true
                    "You sort of bow your head and mumble to yourself. You aren't sure what exactly, for you have no idea what you're doing."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk lovely talk "Might I offer you some assistance, Ghost?"
                        "How do I pray to the nice lady?":
                            choice:
                                talk lovely talk "Just close your eyes, bow your head, and I shall do it for you, hmm?"
                                "[Close your eyes and bow your head]":
                                    talk lovely talk "Ring ring!"
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk lovely talk "Hello, is that Saint Dawnsight?"
                                    talk lovely talk "Yes hello, it's- yes! That's right, it's me, Lovely Lady."
                                    talk lovely talk "Yes."
                                    talk lovely talk "Mhm."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk lovely talk "No she's not very good at this is she."
                                    talk lovely talk "Well- no."
                                    talk lovely talk "Titter titter!"
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk lovely talk "Yes."
                                    talk lovely talk "No."
                                    talk lovely talk "Yes."
                                    talk lovely talk "Yes."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk lovely talk "Well thank you."
                                    talk lovely talk "Yes, I'll send her your best."
                                    talk lovely talk "Toodle ooh now. Mwah, bonsoir mon amie~."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk nasty talk "..."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk lovely talk "Saint Dawnsight says best of luck, Ghost. She hopes things work out for you, and something or other about a flaming sword, I forget."
                                    choice:
                                        talk nasty talk "What the fuck was that? Was that praying?"
                                        "Thank you, Lovely Lady. I feel much more at ease now.":
                                            set data.dawnsight.sawDawnsight true
                                            talk lovely talk "Anytime, darling~"
                                        "I have to concur with Nasty Girl, what the fuck was that?":
                                            talk lovely talk "Oh, suddenly you're an expert at praying, are you Ghost? One thinks this is the last time one will offer up her spiritual services to you! Hmpf! The nerve!"
                        "No thank you. I think she got the message.":
                            talk lovely talk "I'm sure she did, our divine protector is ever vigilant."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "There's a more modest shrine to the Saint in the woods. Hundreds, actually. Perhaps they would serve as a better ambience for your delusions."
                        "I'm not sure if I need to try out religion, but I feel like I should try and talk to Saint Dawnsight some more.":
                            start_quest dawnsight
                            start_objective dawnsight shrine
                            jump church_window_centre_menu
                        "I'm gagging to try out some more religion.":
                            start_quest dawnsight
                            start_objective dawnsight shrine
                            jump church_window_centre_menu
                        "I'd rather choke than try out some more religion.":
                            jump church_window_centre_menu
                        "I'd prefer to do a secret third thing with my throat over trying out some more religion, to be honest ;)":
                            talk lovely talk "Harlot."
                            jump church_window_centre_menu
                "<span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
                    jump church_window_centre_menu
        "Does everyone worship her?":
            talk orb talk "No. Non-Anglian sects of the church view their own leaders who took part in the crusade as saints, and tend to put more emphasis on the crusade as a collective moment of action, rather than the work of a singular person."
            talk orb talk "The peculiar deification of royalty is a *very* Anglian quirk."
            jump church_window_centre_menu
        "I feel like I recognise her.":
            run transition statue_dawnsight_eroded
            talk orb talk "You used to see her every day, or a statue of her, at least. She sat atop the Church of the Distant Saviour, facing out to sea, towards the continent. A hand unfurled south-easterly, as if trying to grab it, to save its soul."
            choice:
                talk orb talk "The Anglian church *loves* weird, nationalistic, misguided self-aggrandising. She didn't look like this though, the Elasia you knew was all empty inside"
                "She was what?":
                    talk orb talk "Erosion. The sea water tore the unprotected elements of her apart bit by bit, year by year, until the woman was gone and all that was left was a husk. The shell of a woman, empty, save for a few flecks of salt."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "She is not so different to the real Dawnsight. The Dawnsight in the eyes of the church is not her. It is something else wearing her skin. Stripped of all of her autonomy, all that is left of her legacy is a husk."
                        "Interesting. Thank you.":
                            talk orb talk "No problem."
                        "The statue was eroded away?":
                            talk orb talk "No, the *actual* Queen Marigold Elasia Dawnsight eroded away in the sea wind a mile away from your apartment in Pawtsmouth. Yes the statue, Ghost."
                        "I feel a great affinity to this statue.":
                            talk orb talk "Mhm."
            run transition church_window_centre
            jump church_window_centre_menu
        "<span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            jump church_window_menu

church_window_left:
    if (!= $data.church.lookingAt "left"):
        run transition church_window_left
    set data.church.lookingAt "left"
    set data.dawnsight.sawWarrior true
    "Queen Marigold Elasia Dawnsight, hoisting an antiquated Anglian flag with pride."
    clear_dialog
    "Behind her march the kings, queens, rulers, khans and sultanates of the nations that followed her on her quest."
    "Flags flutter like butterfly wings; the navy blue of the Franks, the blood red of Brenneburg, the black of the Imperial Inquisition, the... azure of the Azure Horde, the two headed sheep of Muskovy... It's quite a procession."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "Ahead of Dawnsight a great demon spews an evil miasma into the sky. The cloud of darkness morphs into the form of choking faces. If the rest of the Anglian Churches holy beliefs were this exciting the religion would probably be more popular, but alas they are not."
        "Why did she go on her crusade?":
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Legend says she was whispered to by the Divine while lost in the woods just south of your cottage. Some pagan worshippers believe that the queen was deceived by a woodland spirit known as the helpful traveller, though this belief is seen as a grave heresy by the church."
                "<span class='writtenText'>'The Helpful Traveller'</span>?":
                    talk lovely talk "Pah. Nonsense. Heretical nonsense."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk orb talk "A trickster that gives false directions to those who find themselves lost in the woods. Those who follow its advice only find themselves more lost, and when they die of starvation or thirst or exhaustion it feasts on their soul."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "Some believe those who took part in the crusade all fell victim to it, having followed the Queen to her doom, and that it died from overeating."
                        roll church_window_left_orb orb 40 "*Is* that was happened?":
                            success "":
                                set data.church.dawnsightStory true
                                talk orb talk "No. The truth was far simpler. She met a girl in the woods. A pretty one. A peasent, sure, with all the trappings that came with that."
                                talk orb talk "The grey, volcanic dust mottled fur, little different from the industrial soot that blankets you. The raspy ash cough that her majesty had avoided with boiling salt baths. Grime. A curious, but not unpleasant smell... but she was so pretty."
                                talk orb talk "She was also crying."
                                clear_dialog
                                talk orb talk "When Dawnsight asked why the girl replied, between tears, that she missed the blue sky. The <span class='gold'>golden light</span> of sunset through autumnal leaves."
                                talk orb talk "Her village whispered of a great ash demon far to the east that had cast the world into this end time. She cried because none could hope to defeat such a being."
                                talk orb talk "Marigold took her hand, and vowed to put a stop to the Dark Age."
                                clear_dialog
                                talk orb talk "'<span class='goldItalic'>I will see you smile again, my sweet maiden</span>'.' She told the girl."
                                clear_dialog
                                talk orb talk "She did not."
                                talk orb talk "Neither did the girl live to see the last of the ash."
                                clear_dialog
                                talk orb talk "The Dark Age was long. Few saw it through from start to end."
                                jump church_window_menu
                            failure "":
                                talk orb talk "Maybe. Maybe not. It's a fun story though, isn't it."
                                talk lovely talk "Pah. If one enjoys heresy, mayhap."
                                jump church_window_menu
    jump church_window_menu

church_window_right:
    if (!= $data.church.lookingAt "right"):
        run transition church_window_right
    set data.church.lookingAt "right"
    set data.dawnsight.sawCartoon true
    "The third window depicts Queen Marigold Elasia Dawnsight handing out bread to civilians wrapped in the Anglian flag, whilst somehow also hurling a bolt of lightning at a group formed of people waving Imperial flags and holding signs with <span class='writtenText'>'consciencious objector'</span>, <span class='writtenText'>'traitor'</span> and <span class='writtenText'>'I don't dig for victory'</span> written on them."
    clear_dialog
    "This window has a noticeably different style to the others."
    clear_dialog
    if (roll church_window_right_lightning_orb orb 40):
        talk orb talk "This isn't the original image. The old window was struck by a freak bolt of lightning. The glass was shattered and boiled into lava, the metal frame left twisted and melted into ghastly shapes."
        talk nasty talk "That sounds great. They should have kept it like that."
        talk lovely talk "It does sound rather modern. I'll have to suggest the idea to papi for the estate's windows."
        talk orb talk "The church didn't agree. It was quickly replaced."
        talk nasty talk "Pussies."
        clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "It was installed during the war. Apparently one of the patriotic cartoonists for the 'Bluehills Telegraph' was the only artist not currently having their lungs turned to mush by toxic gas at the time."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "You look upon the embarrassing display of wartime patriotism sewn into the fabric of the church."
        "[Wave your fist at the Imperial flags] \\"That's what you deserve, jerries and jerry lovers!\\"":
            talk orb talk "Don't do this in public, please."
            jump church_window_menu
        "[Wave your fist at the Anglian flags] \\"Choke on that bread, Anglian scum.\\" [Look to the side as if there were someone there] \\"I'm one of the good ones.\\"":
            if (!= $data.church.glance true):
                set data.church.glance true
                add data.global.sideGlances 1
                if (>= $data.global.sideGlances 3):
                    unlock_achievement scoops
                    play sound scoopsshutter
                    choice:
                        talk scoops flash "You *are* one of the good ones, Ghost. One of my favourites!"
                        "\\"Holy crackers! There *is* someone there!\\"":
                            talk scoops talk "I've always been there, Ghost!"
                            talk scoops talk "The names Scoops, Scoops McGee. Where there's a story there I'll be!"
                            clear_dialog
                            talk orb talk "CRYPTID CRYPTID CRYPTID THIS IS A CRYPTID."
                            clear_dialog
                            play sound scoopsshutter
                            "Scoops McGee takes another photo of you with his camera."
                            clear_dialog
                            choice:
                                talk scoops talk "Pleasure to meet you mam! But I better scram! Perhaps I'll see you again soon! Like the stars see the moon!"
                                "\\"I love you Scoops McGee!\\"":
                                    set data.cryptids.loveScoops true
                                    "Scoops McGee is gone."
                                "\\"Okay. Bye I guess.\\"":
                                    "Scoops McGee is gone."
                    complete_objective cryptids scoops
                    complete_quest cryptids cryptidsSuccess
                else:
                    play sound scoopscharge
                    "A flicker of motion. A glint, maybe. A breath on the back of your neck."
            else:
                run skip
            jump church_window_menu
        "[Wave one fist at each group of flags] \\"Fuck flags! Fuck you! I hate flags! Fuck you fuck you fuck you!\\" [Stomp up and down a bit]":
            talk nasty talk "Ha ha ha oh my gods she's having a breakdown this is amazing."
            jump church_window_menu